responses.body: {"response": "Welcome to Mockoon's API playground. Be sure to check our documentation at https://mockoon.com/playground/. Enjoy!"}

routes.documentation: Read-only list of pokemons with names in various languages, type and stats (source: https://github.com/fanzeyi/pokemon.json)

headers.value: Content-Type, Origin, Accept, Authorization, Content-Length, X-Requested-With

data.name: Pokemons
Sales
data.value:
[
  {{#repeat 100}}
    { {{setVar 'unitNo' (faker 'number.int' min=1 max=50)}} {{setVar 'unitPrice' (faker 'commerce.price' min=1 max=500)}} {{setVar 'unitCost' (faker 'commerce.price' min=1 max=200)}} {{setVar 'totalRevenue' (multiply @unitNo @unitPrice)}} {{setVar 'totalCost' (multiply @unitCost @unitNo)}} {{setVar 'totalProfit' (subtract @totalRevenue @totalCost)}}
      "id": "{{faker 'string.uuid'}}",
      "country": "{{faker 'location.country'}}",
      "itemType": "{{faker 'commerce.product'}}",
      "salesChannel": "{{faker 'commerce.department'}}",
      "group": "{{faker 'commerce.productAdjective'}}",
      "orderData": "{{faker 'date.past' '10' 'years'}}",
      "shippingDate": "{{faker 'date.soon'}}",
      "units": {{@unitNo}},
      "unitPrice": "{{@unitPrice}}",
      "unitCost": "{{@unitCost}}",
      "totalRevenue": "{{@totalRevenue}}",
      "totalCost": "{{@totalCost}}",
      "totalProfit": "{{@totalProfit}}"
    }
  {{/repeat}}
]
